# Shadcn/UI Component Guidelines

This rule sets standards for installing and using [shadcn/ui](https://ui.shadcn.com/) components.

## Scope
Applies to any change that adds or modifies UI components inside `app/`.

## Installation
1. Use the provided automation:
   ```bash
   bunx shadcn-ui@latest init
   ```
2. Add new components via the helper script (or automated tool):
   ```bash
   bunx shadcn-ui@latest add <component>
   ```
3. **Never** copy-paste source files directly from the repo. Always use the generator so tokens & config stay in sync.

## Configuration Rules
• Keep `tailwind.config.ts` and `components.json` in sync with generator prompts.
• Commit generated components under `components/ui/` — do not rename or move.
• If you need to override a component, prefer creating a thin wrapper instead of editing generated code.

## Styling Conventions
• Components rely on Tailwind **theme** tokens (see `tailwind.config.ts`).
• Use the `cn()` helper for class merging.
• Follow the tailwind-theme rule (see separate rule) — **no hard-coded color classes**.

## Upgrades
• Run `bunx shadcn-ui@latest list:update` to list outdated components.
• Upgrade in small PRs; one component per commit when possible.

Violations should be flagged during code review.